review 1:
Affordable but price reflects on quality. 'A' for effort on creativity. If you're open to trying new taste for sushi, maybe you'd like this place. Some of the sauces were too sweet to my liking. The wasabi wasn't spicy at all and tasted a bit like flour. But again, it's an affordable option for your sushi craving.

The place could also use some work done to make the dine in experience more enjoyable.
